Key placement & validation notes:
• All furniture sits flush on the floor (y ≈ object height / 2 + 0.05).  
• Walls centre at y = 1.55 leaving 0.05 m atop the floor thickness.  
• No object extends beyond room bounds (±4.5 m x, ±5 m z, 3 m y).  
• Desks/chairs grid leaves 0.6 m aisles laterally & 0.8 m longitudinally for easy passage.  
• Teacher desk is 2 m from front wall; whiteboard/clock/projector are wall-mounted or ceiling-hung with safe clearances.  
• Bookshelf (left) and window_with_curtains (right) respect wall thickness offsets to avoid z-fighting.  
• Six ceiling lights form two evenly spaced rows just above wall height, ensuring uniform illumination.
